The paper deals with reasoning under uncertainty and uses Dempster-Shafer theory, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses methods for discounting evidence and inferring events, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with partitioning and subsets, which are concepts commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
